t: To the chief Musician upon Neginah, A Psalm of David.
Hear*p my cry, O God; attend unto my prayer.
From*p the end of the earth will I cry unto thee, when my heart is overwhelmed: lead me to the rock that is higher than I.
For*p thou hast been a shelter for me, and a strong tower from the enemy.
I*p will abide in thy tabernacle for ever: I will trust in the covert of thy wings. Selah.
For*p thou, O God, hast heard my vows: thou hast given me the heritage of those that fear thy name.
Thou*p wilt prolong the king's life: and his years as many generations.
He*p shall abide before God for ever: O prepare mercy and truth, which may preserve him.
So*p will I sing praise unto thy name for ever, that I may daily perform my vows.
